<![CDATA[<div style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" size="6" color="#000066">The British School</font></span></div><div style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="6">of Guangzhou</font></div><div style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="4"><i>Part of The British Schools Group</i></font></div><div style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#c0c0c0" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="6"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="1"><i><br></i></font></div><div style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 5px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 5px; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation}&nbsp;{!Contact.FirstName}&nbsp;{!Contact.LastName},</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Mrs Judith Sanderson,
who has been teaching in Year 4 over the course of the last two months, will be
staying with us until the end of the academic year. This is great news as
Judith has had a real impact on the class and the students are thoroughly
enjoying their lessons. It also minimises further disruption to the year group.<o:p></o:p></font></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="apple-style-span">In addition to this news, I am
also pleased to tell you that Mr Alasdair Carr has been appointed Year 4
Leader. Alasdair has been with us for some time now and his hard work and
dedication make him the perfect person for this role. Please join me in
congratulating him on his appointment.</span><o:p></o:p></font></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="apple-style-span">As stated previously, class sizes
are now at full capacity. Therefore we have made the decision to move to
three-form entry in Year 4. This is a necessary step to ensure that we maintain
the highest quality educational provision. As a result, Miss Michelle McCarthy
will also be joining us from the UK to take up the new Year 4 teaching post.
Miss McCarthy comes with over six years primary teaching experience and will
arrive after the Christmas holidays.</span><o:p></o:p></font></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="apple-style-span">Although we will keep class
changes to a minimum, we will be asking all students to consider three friends
that they would like to be with if they were to move class. If moved, students
would be with at least one of their selected friends. I understand that, in the
short term, students and parents may feel anxious about the outcome. Please be
assured that this will have long term benefit to all concerned. If you would
like to discuss the matter further, please do not hesitate to contact me at </span><a href="mailto:david.laird@bsg.org.cn"><span class="apple-style-span"><span style="color: blue; text-decoration: initial;">david.laird@bsg.org.cn</span></span></a><span class="apple-style-span"> or phone me to make an appointment. My door is always open and I
would encourage you come and see me.</span></font><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></font></p>

